"canned or jarred non gmo apples. the type of fleshy usually rounded and red, yellow, or green edible pome fruit of a tree (genus malus) of the rose family that has been canned or jarred for preservation. this means that they are\u00a0 produced without the use of methods that genetically modify organisms by means that are not possible under natural conditions. \u00a0 such methods include cell fusion, microencapsulation and macro-encapsulation, and recombinant dna technology (including gene deletion, gene doubling, introducing a foreign gene, and changing the positions of genes when achieved by recombinant dna technology). \u00a0 traditional methods of breeding, conjugation, fermentation, hybridization, in vitro fertilization, or tissue culture are considered to be non-gmo.. . "
